    The algorithm first initializes a set `distinct` to keep track of distinct integers in the final array. It then iterates through each integer `num` in the `nums` array, adds the integer `num` to the `distinct` set, and calculates the reversed integer by reversing the digits of `num`. The reversed integer is also added to the `distinct` set. Finally, the algorithm returns the size of the `distinct` set, which represents the number of distinct integers in the final array. The time complexity is O(n) where n is the size of the `nums` array.

